{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow lifeboat crew to use blue lights on private vehicles",
        "additional_details": "In emergencies, lifeboat crews using their own vehicles \u2013 whether they are cars, motorbikes or bicycles \u2013 to get to a lifeboat station can have difficulty passing other vehicles. Road users, pedestrians and local buses often refuse to let them pass. If lifeboat crews could use blue lights they should be able to get to the station and respond to the emergency faster.\r\n\r\nMany of the crew members come from a distance therefore they have to deal with traffic. Allowing blue lights could ultimately reduce response time and save more lives. As we know with other emergency services, minutes save/cost lives.\r\n",
        "background": "Lifeboat crews, including the RNLI, can lose precious minutes battling traffic and lights. Crews must get to a station as quickly as possible. There is currently no way to alert other road users of the emergency. Allowing on-call crew to use blue lights should mean they can travel more quickly.",
